# meta:
#   column_notes: {'*_sum_K': sum of the background-subtracted brightness-temperature model over all 0.1-MHz channels in the window, fmin_MHz/fmax_MHz: 'per-line
#       spectral windows, restfreq*(1 - 16/3e5) to restfreq*(1 + 14/3e5)', molsim_aij_ratio: molsim Einstein A (from co.cat) divided by
#       10**aij computed by pyspeckit get_molecular_parameters from the CDMS LGINT, molsim_tau_ratio: molsim Simulation.spectrum.tau divided
#       by the pyspeckit peak channel tau; the expected value is sqrt(2*pi/(8*ln2)) = 1.0644670 because molsim normalizes the line profile
#       by the FWHM rather than by sqrt(2*pi)*sigma, pyspeckit_peak_tau: peak channel optical depth of the pyspeckit JPL model evaluated
#       on the molsim frequency grid (0.1 MHz channels spanning all windows)}
#   description: 'Reference values for benchmarking the pyspeckit LTE molecule model against XCLASS and molsim for CO v=0 (pyspeckit issue
